  <compounddef id="LEFT" kind="page">
    <compoundname>LEFT</compoundname>
    <title>LEFT$ Function</title>
    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">LEFT$(string-expression,<sp/>integer-expression)</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>Returns the <bold>leftmost characters</bold> from a string. The second parameter specifies how many characters to return.</para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<sect3 id="LEFT_1autotoc_md604">
<title>Examples</title>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">PRINT<sp/>LEFT$(&quot;RetroRocket&quot;,<sp/>5)</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>Produces <computeroutput>Retro</computeroutput>.</para>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">REM<sp/>Extract<sp/>drive<sp/>letter<sp/>from<sp/>a<sp/>path</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">path$<sp/>=<sp/>&quot;C:/users/alice&quot;</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">PRINT<sp/>LEFT$(path$,<sp/>2)</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>Produces <computeroutput>C:</computeroutput>.</para>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">REM<sp/>Safely<sp/>clip<sp/>a<sp/>string</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">msg$<sp/>=<sp/>&quot;Hello,<sp/>world!&quot;</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">PRINT<sp/>LEFT$(msg$,<sp/>80)</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>Prints the message, clipped to 80 characters if longer.</para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
</sect3>
<sect3 id="LEFT_1autotoc_md606">
<title>Notes</title>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>If the length requested is greater than the string length, the entire string is returned.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>If the length is <computeroutput>0</computeroutput>, an empty string is returned.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Negative lengths cause an error.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Result is always a new string, the original is unchanged.</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
